FBIS4-739 "drafr073_d_94010" FBIS-AFR-94-073 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Lesotho Automatic Gunfire Reportedly Heard in Maseru Automatic Gunfire Reportedly Heard in Maseru MB1504052394 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0512 GMT 15 Apr 94 MB1504052394 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [By Jonathan Rees] [Text] Maseru April 15 SAPA -- Several bursts of what is believed to be automatic rifle fire were heard early Friday [15 April] morning in Lesotho's capital, Maseru, where troops on Thursday shot dead Deputy Prime Minister Selometsi Baholo and took four cabinet ministers hostage for a day. It was not clear who was firing or at whom and there was no indication of any formal demands being released by the soldiers.
